text: Togo and the Rise of Japanese Sea Power is a 1936 non-fiction book by Edwin A. Falk, published by Longmans, Green and Co. Bradley A. Fiske, a former rear admiral of the U.S. Navy, gave an introduction. The book is about Tōgō Heihachirō. ==References== * * * - Published online on 2 September 2013. * * ===Notes=== ==External links== * Togo and the Rise of Japanese Sea Power - Available at the Internet Archive * Category:1937 non-fiction books Category:History books about Japan Category:Tōgō Heihachirō
title: Togo and the Rise of Japanese Sea Power
